      "name": "Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Extract from receipts with Google Drive and Google Sheets for your team\n\n**Pattern:** File Processing · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nExtract from receipts with Google Drive and Google Sheets for your team. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual contracts is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Export All Rows (Google Sheets) → Serialize to CSV → Compress Archive → Upload Backup to Google Drive → Backup Size Sane? → Tag Pipeline Metadata → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to file processing without manual effort\n- Anyone automating contracts in legal\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "1ae3acd5-3714-bcb9-cb55-b110b5234ed2",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "6b289289-0ab2-7981-1231-691b33feea64",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your contracts process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
